00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:09,860
Right!

257
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:13,370
Where are the diagrams of the 
transmutation circles from the 5th Laboratory?!

258
00:14:13,370 --> 00:14:15,970
The budget from the first year of the Ishbal Rebellion!

259
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:21,340
Am I going to get 
overtime pay for this?

260
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:23,230
I'll give you a picture of Elicia!

261
00:14:28,180 --> 00:14:33,080
Ishbal... Liore... Mugear's mines...

262
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:36,680
Once they got near a Philosopher's Stone, 
they were destroyed.

263
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:38,620
Strange, isn't it?

264
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:42,790
If they're driving people to 
create a Philosopher's Stone,

265
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,410
why would they spread stories around

266
00:14:44,410 --> 00:14:47,190
that destruction befalls those who seek the Philosopher's Stone?

267
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:50,510
Is it to get rid of all the evidence?

268
00:14:50,510 --> 00:14:52,830
No... It couldn't be...

269
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,040
just the opposite, could it?

270
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,540
Supposing everything was reversed...

271
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:03,540
Hold on... The unit that caused 
the outbreak of war in Ishbal was...

272
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:06,040
...Douglas? Where have 
I heard that name before?

273
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:08,840
Um, there's a phone call 
from the Führer's secretary.

274
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:13,910
Yes, Doctor Marcoh has arrived in Central.

275
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:15,350
He is waiting at the hotel.

276
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:18,370
Thank you very much. 
I will go see him right away.

277
00:15:22,260 --> 00:15:24,830
Douglas... Juliet...

278
00:15:26,340 --> 00:15:30,320
Scieszka! Put all of these materials back where you found them!

279
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:34,450
Once that's done, you can go home! 
Also, you're fired!

280
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:35,830
Don't ever come around here again.

281
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:41,330
Sorry to put you 
through all this trouble.

282
00:15:41,330 --> 00:15:44,300
Ms. Secretary... Douglas-san,

283
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:46,850
do you know much 
about the Ishbalan War?

284
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:49,810
No, I have always had desk jobs.

285
00:15:49,810 --> 00:15:51,090
So have I, you know?

286
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:54,700
I've been looking into 
some things lately.

287
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:57,780
Did you know that the reason the rebellion broke out

288
00:15:57,780 --> 00:16:03,310
was that one of the soldiers stationed there recklessly shot and killed an Ishbalan child?

289
00:16:03,310 --> 00:16:07,560
That soldier's name, 
it turns out, was Juliet Douglas.

290
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,320
It's a common name.

291
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:14,390
That's where it gets interesting. The soldier with that name

292
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:18,200
was supposed to have died two years before the Ishbal Rebellion.

293
00:16:18,430 --> 00:16:19,920
That is odd.

294
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:22,210
There's one other "odd" thing.

295
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:25,000
Douglas was dead before then.

296
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,210
And yet the muster roll for this person 
named Juliet Douglas was never withdrawn.

297
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:32,640
On the contrary, 
over the last two years,

298
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:36,220
the soldier with that name 
has been suddenly promoted.

299
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,970
And now, she has been promoted to the Führer's Ministerial Secretary?

300
00:16:41,830 --> 00:16:44,480
Who are you?

301
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,620
Were you at Ishbal?

302
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:51,130
Or did you just use Douglas's 
registration to get into the military?

303
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,820
The Doctor is waiting.

304
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:58,530
Is that even Marcoh 
behind that door?

305
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:03,000
Nice to meet you.

306
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,420
Or perhaps, "farewell" 
might be more appropriate.

307
00:17:06,740 --> 00:17:09,170
That's a cool tattoo 
you've got there, sweetheart.

308
00:17:12,210 --> 00:17:13,010
Lt. Colonel!

309
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:23,020
That was unexpectedly skillful, huh?

310
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:26,730
Sloth, make sure to let everyone know.

311
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:33,550
Lieutenant Ross, 
they're right next to the Führer!

312
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:37,240
The enemy has fully infiltrated the military. Their purpose...

313
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:40,160
is not to create a Philosopher's Stone.

314
00:17:41,210 --> 00:17:42,240
No...

315
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,180
Come with me.

316
00:17:44,180 --> 00:17:45,250
Yes, sir.

317
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,980
Ah, dammit...

318
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:51,550
Jeez, what a pain...

319
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,880
What? He's not there?!

320
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:58,580
He left for Central with Lieutenant Hawkeye.

321
00:17:58,580 --> 00:18:00,010
Has something happened?

322
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,760
With this information,

323
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:05,280
he had a chance to rise 
right to the top!

324
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:07,730
In any event, we should get to someplace safe.

325
00:18:07,730 --> 00:18:11,730
You're right. It's not as though 
I've got nothing left to hang onto.

326
00:18:12,130 --> 00:18:14,440
Why don't you 
tell me all about it?

327
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:19,080
The Lieutenant has a mole under one of her eyes.

328
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:21,870
Is that right?

329
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:23,990
I must have gotten careless.

330
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,660
That's amazing.

331
00:18:41,320 --> 00:18:43,070
Forgive me.

332
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:46,080
I have a wife and daughter waiting for me at home.

333
00:18:51,140 --> 00:18:54,640
That was a pretty good act, 
wasn't it, Lt. Colonel Hughes?

334
00:19:08,890 --> 00:19:11,400
I'm going to become the Führer.

335
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:15,520
I'm going to change 
the way this country runs.

336
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:18,130
That's the only thing I can do.

337
00:19:18,510 --> 00:19:24,010
Then you'll need someone who 
understands you and can support you.

338
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:29,700
Someone underneath you, who can push you upward.

339
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:24,780
Mama, why? Why are they burying Papa?

340
00:20:25,870 --> 00:20:29,810
Huh? Why are those men burying Papa?

341
00:20:29,810 --> 00:20:30,970
Why?

342
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,000
Elicia...

343
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,530
I don't want them to.

344
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:35,810
I don't want them to!

345
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:39,880
If they do that, then Papa 
can't do his work anymore!

346
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,760
Mama, stop them!

347
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,470
Elicia...

348
00:20:43,470 --> 00:20:46,900
Papa said he still had 
a lot of work to do!

349
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,580
I don't want them to!

350
00:20:49,420 --> 00:20:51,940
Don't bury him! Mama!

351
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:54,970
Papa! Papa!

352
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:13,160
Killed in the line of duty and 
posthumously promoted two ranks...

353
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,210
Brigadier General Hughes, huh?

354
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:20,790
What am I going to do 
now that the man who said

355
00:21:20,790 --> 00:21:24,630
